It&#39;s great how they can grow and split however I hate how the resulting
slimes after split have half the experiance of the slime which split to form
them (and also how they become part of your team).
I suggest that the split ability of slimes works more like summoning, the
slime splits and forms two however the main one retains everything and the
one split of is at a % of skills/level/etc of the parent and that percent is
higher with higher levels of the parent slime.

Alternatively you could have the slimes level controlling how many others
can split off from it, sort of like a control factor/summoning limit.

Most importantly I don&#39;t want the newly split slimes to become a permanent
part of your team, its very annoying to have the team roster filled with 100
new slime after a battle :)

Of course all this shouldn&#39;t apply to slime not on the players team, in that
case they should be able to split but are weakened differently (ie they
might stay at the same level but grow slower).

- Deathifier

